OL,5, People with recurrent illness caused by
OL,6, hard-to-treat bacterium Clostridium    
OL,7, difficile can be offered faecal        
OL,8, transplants, the National Institute for
OL,9, Health and Care Excellence has said.   
OL,11,FC. diff can cause infection if the     
OL,12,Fbalance of bowel bacteria changes -    
OL,13,Fafter taking antibiotics, for example. 
OL,15,FThe transplants transfer beneficial gut
OL,16,Fbacteria from a healthy donor's faeces.
OL,18,FClinical trials show they are more     
OL,19,Feffective than antibiotics, to which   
OL,20,Fthis "superbug" can become resistant.  
